      • isReady

        boolean isReady()
        Gets ready status of the request. Note that results obtained from NCClient.check(Set, Integer, Long, String) method can be in not-ready state indicating that they are submitted but still being processed. Results returned from NCClient.askSync(String, String) or NCClient.askSync(String, String, String, boolean, Long, String) methods are always ready.
        Returns:
        Ready status of the request.

      • getResultType

        Gets the result type. See NCQueryResult class for details.
        Returns:
        Query result type.

      • getResultBody

        String getResultBody()
        Gets the result body as stringified JSON object. See NCQueryResult class for details.
        Returns:
        Query result body.

      • getErrorCode

        Integer getErrorCode()
        Gets optional error code. See /check operation in openapi/nlpcraft_swagger.yml file for more details. Note that error code and error message are only present if query result is unsuccessful.
        Returns:
        Optional error code. Can be null.

      • getErrorMessage

        String getErrorMessage()
        Gets optional error message. Note that error code and error message are only present if query result is unsuccessful.
        Returns:
        Optional error message. Can be null.

      • getLogHolder

        String getLogHolder()
        Gets optional processing log holder. When not null this string contains JSON object representing processing log.
        Returns:
        Optional processing log. Can be null.
